<article>
    <h1>Get your fix of lac&#xAD;tose-free milk</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201228/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-28"><time>2020-12-28</time></a>
        - <span>SINGAPORE</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>Meiji has launched a new size and flavour for their pop­u­lar Meiji Lac­tose Free Milk, which was first re­leased in 2019. The lead­ing milk brand is re­spond­ing to the over­whelm­ing re­sponse by in­tro­duc­ing a new 946ml ver­sion as well as a new dark cho­co­late flavour.</p>
    <p>With lac­tose-free milk, lac­tose in­tol­er­ant users who are de­prived of the nu­tri­tion that cow’s milk pro­vides can now en­joy the ben­e­fits of milk with­out hav­ing to en­dure di­ges­tive is­sues.</p>
    <p>The orig­i­nal flavour vari­ant con­tains cal­cium and Vi­ta­min B12, and has no added sugar. It comes in a 200ml bot­tle and 946ml gable top box. The dark cho­co­late flavour milk con­tains cal­cium and Vi­ta­min B2, and is trans fat free. It comes in a 946ml gable top box.</p>
    <p>Look out for Meiji lac­tose-free milk prod­ucts in gro­cery shelves is­land­wide.</p>

